Iris — Licensing
================

Iris consists of a core type-bridge library and an OS utility layer.
The core is GPL-2.0; the OS utility layer (src/os/, include/os.hpp)
is Apache-2.0 so it can be embedded freely without copyleft propagation.

Copyright (c) 2026 Iris Contributors.


Components
----------

  Core  (src/, include/ — except os.hpp)   GNU General Public License v2.0
                                            → https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.html

  OS utilities  (src/os/, include/os.hpp)   Apache License, Version 2.0
                                            → https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0


Summary
-------

You may use, modify, and redistribute the core under the terms of the
GNU General Public License v2.0.  Any derived work that incorporates
the core must be distributed under the same license.

The OS utility layer (ls, ps, env commands and their type definitions)
is released under the Apache License 2.0 and may be incorporated into
proprietary or differently-licensed projects without restriction,
provided the Apache 2.0 attribution requirements are met.

OS utility source files carry the identifier:
  // SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
